kamahi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Weinmannia</i> spp. often confused in popular terminology with beech (birch) species, esp. perhaps <i>towai</i> through similarity with <i>tawhai</i> (beech), hence popular misapplication of <i>kamahi</i> to <i>Nothofagus </i>spp.: some distinguish <i>towai</i> as <i>W. sylvicola</i> only; others apply <i>towai</i> to both spp. (so Williams) reserving <i>kamahi</i> (and <i>tawhero</i>) for W. racemosa only; a tall, spreading forest tree
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: red birch
Pronunciation:
Notes:
